    <briefdescription>
<para>Forward POSIX termination signals to a regular worker thread. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>The async signal handler only writes the received signal number into a pipe. The watcher thread reads that pipe and invokes the configured callback in a normal thread context, where terminal cleanup can safely use locks and iostreams. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
